  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nStatus dapp browser requires the chainId to be defined when signing transactions using eip712 domain typeddata, even though this field is defined as optional in the [eip712 spec](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-712.md#definition-of-domainseparator).\n\n```\nProtocol designers only need to include the fields that make sense for their signing domain. Unused fields are left out of the struct type.\n```\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nTo be able to sign a transaction on networks that don't include the chainId in their signing hash.\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nSigning transactions fail because chainId is missing in the typedData. \n\n#### Notes\n\nSigning transactions without the chainId works in all other dapp browsers except Status.\n\n![81656652-65454b00-9461-11ea-8a53-62ef88c791b8](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29919550/81917245-21884800-95ff-11ea-8bbe-aea9be6c48cc.png)",
